<topic template="Default" lasteditedby="Liset" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">XS0650</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">XS0650</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">XS0650</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Bad array declarator: To declare a managed array the rank specifier precedes the variable&apos;s identifier. To declare a fixed size buffer field, use the fixed keyword before the field type.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An array was declared incorrectly. In X#, unlike in C and C++, the square brackets follow the type, not the variable name. Also, realize that the syntax for a fixed size buffer differs from that of an array.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example code generates XS0650.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// XS0650.prg  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public class MyClass  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   public static void Main()  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">   {  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// Generates XS0650. Incorrect array declaration syntax:  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      int myarray[2];     </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // Correct declaration.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      int[] myarray2;  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // Declaration and initialization in one statement  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      int[] myArray3= new int[2] {1,2}  </text><br/><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      // Access an array element.  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">      myarray3[0] = 0;  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">    }  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">}  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2"><text styleclass="Heading2" translate="true">Example</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The following example shows how to use the fixed keyword when you create a fixed size buffer:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Code with box"><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">// This code must appear in an unsafe block.   </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">public struct MyArray   </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">{  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">    public fixed char pathName[128];  </text><br/><text styleclass="Code with box" translate="true">}  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">  </text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
  </body>
